25|$|Typically, a pinion-operated rack moving {{parallel}} to the (trig.-defined) opposite side would position a slide with a slot coincident with the <b>hypotenuse.</b> A pivot on the rack let the slide's angle change freely. At {{the other end of}} the slide (the angle, in trig, terms), a block on a pin fixed to the frame defined the vertex between the <b>hypotenuse</b> and the adjacent side.|$|E
